{
  "genre": "hiphop",
  "mode": "focus",
  "mixStrategy": "This hip hop focus track is built around an i \u2192 bVI \u2192 bVII \u2192 i progression in Am (Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am), cycling every 6.4 seconds (8 beats at 75 BPM). The arrangement is designed for steady, habituating focus with minimal surprises.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION: The Synth Bass (38) anchors the sub-bass region (MIDI 33-45, ~55-110Hz) with long sustained root notes that lock with the kick drum. The Warm Pad (89) fills the mid-range (MIDI 52-67, ~260Hz-1.2kHz) with dark minor chord voicings that evolve slowly. The Vibraphone melody (11) sits in the upper-mid/presence range (MIDI 64-79, ~523Hz-3kHz) with short, looping bell-like motifs. Drums provide rhythmic scaffolding across the spectrum.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: Kick and bass lock together on beats 1 and 3. Snare/clap punctuates beats 2 and 4 (boom-bap). Hi-hats provide 8th-note texture with velocity variations for groove. The melody plays behind-the-beat phrases that breathe in the spaces between drum hits, creating a laid-back feel.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments, ~7.5s each): 0.4 \u2192 0.6 \u2192 0.7 \u2192 0.7 \u2192 0.7 \u2192 0.5. The track enters softly with bass and sparse melody, drums enter lightly in segment 2, full texture by segment 3, sustains through segments 4-5, then gently recedes in segment 6. Velocity stays in the 45-75 range for melody/chords to maintain focus-friendly consistency.\n\nHARMONIC PLAN (each cycle = 6.4s):\nCycle 1 (0.0-6.4): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 2 (6.4-12.8): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 3 (12.8-19.2): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 4 (19.2-25.6): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 5 (25.6-32.0): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 6 (32.0-38.4): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\nCycle 7 (38.4-44.8): Am \u2192 F \u2192 G \u2192 Am\n\nThis creates a hypnotic loop that habituates within the first two cycles, ideal for deep focus.",
